# Adapted from the public Check Point community thread:
# https://community.checkpoint.com/t5/Security-Gateways/Firewall-and-Content-Awareness-Blade-missing-license/td-p/114613
# The forum post shows licensing rows as a rendered table (ID, Blade name, Entitlement status, Expiration date),
# not as a raw snmpwalk. This fixture re-encodes only those public values into the Check Point licensing table
# shape so we can validate real blade names, real state strings, the max-uint32 sentinel, and real epoch values.
# The SNMP row index is not shown in the forum post, so this adapted fixture uses the public IDs as row indexes.
